      <h1 class="title">A tribute to Steve Jobs </h1>
    <h3> Who is Steve Jobs? </h3>
      <p> Steve Jobs was a charismatic pioneer of the personal computer era. With Steve Wozniak, Jobs founded Apple Inc. in 1976 and transformed the company into a world leader in telecommunications. Widely considered a visionary and a genius, he oversaw the launch of such revolutionary products as the iPod and the iPhone. </p>
    <h3> Why we admire him? </h3>
        <p>
      His commitment to one purpose, single-mindedness, and ability to follow his heart beyond the established stereotypes are the main qualities I most admire about Steve Jobs.
    </p>
    <h3> His accomplishments </h3>
        <p>
          Heres a list of what he's accomplished so far!
          <ul>
            <li>Igniting the personal computer revolution</li>
          <li>Introducing the mouse and graphical user interface.</li>
          <li>Bringing portable music players to the masses.</li>
          <li>Revolutionizing the sale of music</li>
          <li>Shepherding the age of computer animation</li>
          <li>Opening Apple stores</li>
          <li>Making personal computers stylish</li>
          <li>Launching the smartphone revolution</li>
          <li>Changing how software applications are distributed</li>
    </ul>
    </p>
  </body>
